/Q24: Write a program to calculate electricity bill based on units consumed with these rates: 
First 100 units at ₹5/unit 
Next 100 units at ₹7/unit 
Next 100 units at ₹10/unit 
Above at ₹12/unit

/*
Sample Test Cases:
Input 1:
50
Output 1:
Bill: ₹250

Input 2:
150
Output 2:
Bill: ₹850

Input 3:
250
Output 3:
Bill: ₹1700

*/ 

source code :
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int unit;
    int bill = 0;

    printf("Enter the number of unit of electricity consumed: ");
    scanf("%d", &unit);

    if (unit <= 100) {
        bill= unit*5;
        printf("Bill ₹%d\n", bill );
    }
    else if (unit<= 200) {
        bill = (100*5) + ((unit-100) * 7);
        printf("Bill ₹%d\n", bill );
    }
    else if (unit <= 300) {
        bill = (100*5) + (100*7) + ((unit-200)*10);
        printf("Bill ₹%d\n", bill );
    }
    else   {
        bill= (100*5) + (100*7) +(100*10) +((unit-300)*12);
        printf("Bill ₹%d\n", bill );
    }
    

    return 0;
}
